INSERT INTO `seminars` VALUES
(1,'topology',NULL,1,'2014年4月25日','Equivalence between embedded contact homology and Heegaard-Floer homology via open book decompositions','Vincent Colin','Université de Nante','16:30 - 17:30','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 61125号室','In a work in common with Paolo Ghiggini and Ko Honda, we exibit an isomorphism between Heegaard Floer homology and embedded contact homology for any contact manifold of dimension three (M,ξ). It is constructed from an open book decomposition of M supporting ξ.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(2,'topology',NULL,2,'2017年5月29日','Non-commutative Differential Calculus and the Goldman-Turaev Lie bialgebra','Florian Naef','Université de Genève','16:30 - 17:50','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 61125号室','Using the intersection and self-intersection of loops on a surface one can define the Goldman-Turaev Lie bialgebra. This structure can be extended to the group algebra of the fundamental group, where it can be understood in terms of a kind of non-commutative differential calculus. On a genus zero surface with three boundary components the linearization problem of this structure is equivalent to the Kashiwara-Vergne problem in Lie theory. Motivated by this result a generalization of the Kashiwara-Vergne problem in higher genera is proposed and solutions are constructed in analogy with elliptic associators.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(3,'topology',NULL,3,'2017年6月30日','Splitting theorems for Poisson and related structures','Eckhard Meinrenken','Univ.Toronto','16:30 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 12階 61225室','According to the Weinstein splitting theorem, any Poisson manifold is locally, near any given point m, a product of a symplectic manifold with another Poisson manifold whose Poisson bivector field vanishes at m. Similar splitting results exist for Lie algebroids, anchored vector bundles, Dirac structures, generalized complex structures and so on. I will explain a new approach towards these results, leading to more precise versions and generalizations. (Based on joint work with Henrique Bursztyn and Hudson Lima.)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(4,'topology',NULL,4,'2018年4月5日','Introduction to Novikov homology','Andrei Pajitnov','Univ. de Nantes','16:00 - 17:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 12階 61225室',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(5,'topology',NULL,5,'2018年5月11日','Deformations and normal forms of differential-graded manifolds and related structures','Arkady Vaintrob','University of Oregon, USA','16:30 - 17:30','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 11階 61125B室','A differential-graded (DG) manifold is a manifold with a sheaf of quasi-free commutative differential graded algebras. They are also sometimes called Q-manifolds or supermanifolds with homological vector fields. I will first present general results about deformations and local normal forms of DG-manifolds. Then I will explain how they can be used to study more traditional geometric structures, such as Poisson manifolds, Lie algebroids, Lie bialgebroids, generalized complex manifolds, etc.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(6,'topology',NULL,6,'2018年5月25日','Uniform relative stability and coercivity for polarized toric manifolds','新田 泰文','東京理科大学・理学部','16:30 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 12階 61202室','We study a connection between an algebro-geometric stability and the growth of the modified K-energy which characterizes the extremal Kähler metric as a critical point. In this talk, we introduce uniform relative K-polystability for polarized toric manifolds and show that it implies the coercivity of the modified K-energy modulo the maximal torus action. If time allows, we will explain a sufficient condition for uniform relative K-polystability of polarized toric manifolds. This talk is based on a joint work with Shunsuke Saito and Naoto Yotsutani.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(7,'topology',NULL,7,'2018年6月8日','Twistor spaces, Del Pezzo fibrations, and quartic hypersurfaces','本多 宣博','東京工業大学・理学院','16:30 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 12階 61202室','4次元多様体上の反自己双対計量にはツイスター空間とよばれる3次元複素多様体が付随する。本講演では、コンパクトツイスター空間のうち、特殊な形をした単独の多変数4次多項式により記述できるものについて最近得られた結果を紹介する。これらの空間はDel Pezzo曲面による（有理）ファイブレーションの構造を持ち、代数的なツイスター空間全体の中でかなり大きな部分を占める。',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(8,'topology',NULL,8,'2018年6月23日','2次元ラグランジュセルフ-シュリンカーについて','成 慶明','福岡大学・理学部','15:00 - 16:30','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 12階 61202室','本講演では、平均曲率フローのセルフ-シュリンカーに関する結果を紹介し、第2基本形式の長さが一定となる2次元完備セルフ-シュリンカーを考えます。特に、4次元ユークリッド空間内の第2基本形式の長さが一定となる2次元完備ラグランジュセルフ-シュリンカーの分類を解説します。',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(9,'topology',NULL,9,'2018年11月23日','Foulon surgery, new contact flows and complexity','Boris Hasselblatt','Tufts University','16:30 - 17:45','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 12階 61225室','A refinement of Dehn surgery produces new contact flows that are unusual and interesting in several ways. The geodesic flow of a hyperbolic surface becomes a nonalgebraic contact Anosov flow with larger orbit growth, and the purely periodic fiber flow becomes parabolic or hyperbolic. Moreover, Reeb flows for other contact forms for the same contact structure have the same complexity. Finally, an idea by Vinhage promises a quantification of the complexity increase.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(10,'topology',NULL,10,'2019年3月11日-14日','Workshop \"Geometric Analysis in Geometry and Topology 2018\"','Eric Bahuaud, Renato Bettiol, Boris Botvinnik, Kei Irie','Seattle University, City University of New York, University of Oregon, University of Tokyo','10:00 - 16:30','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 11階 61125室','Research workshop \"Geometric Analysis in Geometry and Topology 2018\" held at Chuo University (Korakuen Campus).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(11,'topology',NULL,11,'2019年4月19日','Weinstein flexibility and its applications','Yakov Eliashberg','Stanford University / 京都大学数理解析研究所','17:00 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 11階 61125室','I’ll survey the notion and applications of flexibility for Weinstein symplectic manifolds including recent results (mainly due to Oleg Lazarev).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(12,'topology',NULL,12,'2019年9月21日-25日','The First Geometry Conference for Friendship of Japan and Germany',NULL,'Chuo University',NULL,'中央大学 後楽園キャンパス 6号館 61125号室','The First Geometry Conference for Friendship of Japan and Germany held at Chuo University (Korakuen Campus), 6th building, Room 61125.',NULL,NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Program / Abstracts\",\"url\":\"/pdf/JG1st.pdf\"}]',NULL),
(13,'topology',NULL,13,'2019年10月25日','SL(2,C)内の複素平均曲率一定曲面の表現公式','糸 健太郎','名古屋大学・多元数理','17:00 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 61202号室','SL(2,C)は複素3次元球面と同一視でき，その中に実3次元空間形 S^3, H^3, dS^3, AdS^3 を含む。Aiyama–Akutagawa の一連の仕事により，これら空間形の中の平均曲率一定曲面に関する表現公式が得られているが，ここではこの仕事の一般化として，SL(2,C)内の複素平均曲率一定曲面に関する表現公式を与える。時間が許せば，双曲幾何への応用について考えていることにも言及したい。',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(14,'topology',NULL,14,'2019年11月22日','Poisson structures and homology groups of Lie superalgebras','三上 健太郎','秋田大学','17:00 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 61202号室','First we recall doubly weighted Lie superalgebra and its (co)homology theory, which is a generalization of weighted Lie algebra and its (co)homology theory. Then we discuss Euler number and Betti numbers of doubly weighted homology groups of a concrete Lie superalgebra which is familiar in Poisson geometry.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(15,'topology',NULL,15,'2020年1月17日','Relative K-stabilities on polarized toric manifolds','斎藤 俊輔','理化学研究所AIPセンター','17:00 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 61202号室','This talk will concern relations between algebro-geometric stabilities for polarized manifolds. To ensure the existence of canonical metrics, many authors proposed stronger concepts of the notion of K-stability. These are divided into two strategies: one is “uniform stability” and the other is “stability tested by more objects than test configurations”. In this talk, I will show that these two approaches are equivalent on polarized toric manifolds. As a consequence, we solve a uniform version of the Yau–Tian–Donaldson conjecture for Calabi’s extremal K\"ahler metrics in the toric setting. This is based on a joint work with Yasufumi Nitta.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(16,'topology',NULL,16,'2022年7月1日','Gravitational instantons, rational surfaces, and K3 surfaces','Jeff Viaclovsky','University of California, Irvine','17:00 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 61125B号室','I will describe some examples of complete non-compact Ricci-flat metrics in dimension 4, which are called \"gravitational instantons.\" In many cases, these can be compactified complex analytically to rational surfaces. I will also discuss how these gravitational instantons can arise from sequences of degenerating Ricci-flat metrics on the compact K3 surface, through a process called \"bubbling\".',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(17,'topology',NULL,17,'2022年10月13日','Euler-like Vector Fields and Normal Forms','Eckhard Meinrenken','University of Toronto','17:00 - 18:00','中央大学 理工学部 6号館 61225号室','A vector field on a manifold is “Euler-like” with respect to a submanifold if its linear approximation is the Euler vector field on the normal bundle. We show that such a vector field canonically determines a tubular neighborhood embedding, and use this fact to obtain several normal form results in differential geometry. This talk is based in part on work with Francis Bischoff, Henrique Bursztyn, Hudson Lima, and Yiannis Loizides.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(18,'topology',NULL,18,'2024年7月27日','Geometry, Topology or Something',NULL,'中央大学, 東京工業大学, 東海大学, 東京都立大学, 明治大学, お茶の水女子大学','13:40 - 17:00','中央大学 後楽園キャンパス 6号館 61239号室','プログラム\n・13:40~14:00 山﨑 雄一郎（中央大学）\n	ウェイト多様体の体積関数とコホモロジー環について\n・14:00~15:00 直江 央寛（東京工業大学）\n	4 次元多様体の組み合わせ的表示と不変量\n・15:00~15:30 小川 竜（東海大学）\n	接触構造の圧縮性を用いた Liouville 領域の構成\n・15:30~16:00 赤穂まなぶ（東京都立大学）\n	Subtorus actions on Grassmannians and polygon spaces\n・16:00~16:20 髙倉 樹（中央大学）\n	On Chern numbers of weight varieties\n・16:20~16:40 三好 重明（中央大学）\n	非特異モース・スメイル流の定める葉層のホモロジー\n・16:40~17:00 Problem Session（佐藤 篤之（明治大学），大場 清（お茶の水女子大学）他）',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(19,'topology',NULL,19,'2025年11月7日','The L p Laplace spectrum of conformally compact manifolds','Julie Rowlett','Chalmers University, Sweden','17:00 - 18:00','中央大学 後楽園キャンパス 6号館 61125B号室','This talk is about joint work with Nelia Charalambous (Cyprus). Conformally compact manifolds are a class of non-compact manifolds with variable curvature that were introduced in their full generality by Fefferman and Graham to study conformal invariants. They are a broad class and include many physical examples like manifolds with Poincaré–Einstein metrics. Despite significant interest in these spaces, there is relatively little known about their Laplace spectra. Unlike some geometric settings in which the L p Laplace spectrum is independent of p, we will see here that the L p Laplace spectrum on a conformally compact manifold depends not only on p but also on the geometry of the manifold.',NULL,NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Program / Abstracts\",\"url\":\"/pdf/2025_JulieRowlett.pdf\"}]',NULL),
